Reasoning: The paper discusses the development and improvement of a camera-based tactile sensor for manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of raw skin deformation data for control and learning tasks involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The application of the proposed controllers in a challenging assembly task also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
